{
  "stem": "2004.5",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "They were some political prisoners.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "Now, the politicals were kept separate.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "They had an insignia, like a red insignia.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And they were, from the Germans, they were the most humane ones, were the political prisoners.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "They were communists, actually.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "But they, basically, did not have a very high opinion of the other German prisoners.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "Now the Germans, through the administration, which was the blockalteste and the captain of the block-- they were all Germans.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "They lived in the same thing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "But they, they, they, they were in charge of rations.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "They were in charge of everything inside the camp.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "These people, I heard them talk.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "They were really talking already.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "They knew that the Americans were getting close, that the war is coming to an end.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "But they were going to line up in the last day with the SS and fight on the side of the Germans against us, in case we ever tried something funny.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "If we tried to revolt against the guards, they were not-- they were going to line up with the Germans and helped the Germans, he says, because their hope was-- he says, we are Germans, and we must protect our nation.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "Even though they were prisoners, and they were in a concentration camp, they considered themselves Germans, and they were proud Germans.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "So no matter what-- no matter what, in the last minute, we could not ever count on them being on our side.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "They were going to join with the SS, and they were hoping that the SS were going to give them weapons, and they were hoping that they were going to help the SS exterminate us, the Jews.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So basically, we had an enemy within, and we had an enemy outside.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The outside enemy, of course, was the SS.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
